{
  "diffMode": "text",
  "formatName": "SSH Private Key (OpenSSH)",
  "version": "1.0",
  "extensions": [ ".pem", ".key", ".id_rsa", ".id_ed25519" ],
  "description": "SSH private key files in OpenSSH native or legacy PEM format. OpenSSH native format (default since OpenSSH 6.5, 2014): '-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----' + base64 + '-----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----'. Binary structure inside: magic 'openssh-key-v1' + NUL + cipher_name (none or aes256-ctr/cbc) + kdf_name (none or bcrypt) + kdf_options (salt+rounds for bcrypt) + number_of_keys + public_key_data + private_key_data (possibly encrypted). Legacy PEM formats: '-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----' (PKCS#1 RSA), '-----BEGIN DSA PRIVATE KEY-----' (DSA), '-----BEGIN EC PRIVATE KEY-----' (SEC 1 EC), '-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----' (PKCS#8 unencrypted), '-----BEGIN ENCRYPTED PRIVATE KEY-----' (PKCS#8 AES-256-CBC encrypted). Passphrase protection: AES-256-CTR + bcrypt KDF (modern) or AES-128-CBC + MD5 (legacy PEM DEK-Info header). Key types: RSA, ECDSA (P-256/P-384/P-521), Ed25519, FIDO/U2F sk-* variants.",
  "category": "Certificates",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "hex-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "OpenSSH PROTOCOL.key — openssh.com native key format specification",
      "RFC 4716 — SSH Public Key File Format",
      "RFC 5958 — Asymmetric Key Packages (PKCS#8)"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://www.openssh.com/",
      "https://cvsweb.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/src/usr.bin/ssh/PROTOCOL.key",
      "https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4716"
    ]
  },
  "detection": {
    "signatures": [
      { "value": "2D2D2D2D2D424547494E204F50454E5353482050524956415445204B4559", "offset": 0, "label": "-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY — modern OpenSSH native private key format", "weight": 1.0 },
      { "value": "2D2D2D2D2D424547494E205253412050524956415445204B4559", "offset": 0, "label": "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY — legacy PEM PKCS#1 RSA private key", "weight": 0.95 },
      { "value": "2D2D2D2D2D424547494E20454320505249564154452044455920", "offset": 0, "label": "-----BEGIN EC PRIVATE KEY — legacy PEM SEC 1 EC private key", "weight": 0.95 },
      { "value": "2D2D2D2D2D424547494E2050524956415445204B4559", "offset": 0, "label": "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY — PKCS#8 unencrypted private key", "weight": 0.9 }
    ],
    "matchMode": "any",
    "MinimumScore": 0.9,
    "required": true,
    "Strength": "Strong",
    "validation": {
      "minFileSize": 27,
      "maxSignatureOffset": 0,
      "note": "All SSH private key formats use PEM-style armor headers starting at offset 0. The specific header text uniquely identifies the key format and type."
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "firstByte": 0,
    "pemHeader": ""
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First Byte",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 1,
      "color": "#FF6B6B",
      "opacity": 0.4,
      "description": "First byte of the key file. Always 0x2D (hyphen '-') for all PEM-format private keys, indicating a '-----BEGIN' armor header. Any other value indicates a non-PEM (binary DER) format or a corrupted file.",
      "storeAs": "firstByte",
      "valueType": "uint8"
    },
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "name": "PEM Armor Header",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 27,
      "color": "#4ECDC4",
      "opacity": 0.45,
      "description": "PEM armor header identifying the key type. Values: '-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----' (modern Ed25519/ECDSA/RSA), '-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----' (legacy PKCS#1 RSA), '-----BEGIN EC PRIVATE KEY-----' (legacy SEC 1 ECDSA), '-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----' (PKCS#8 unencrypted), '-----BEGIN ENCRYPTED PRIVATE KEY-----' (PKCS#8 encrypted).",
      "storeAs": "pemHeader",
      "valueType": "ascii"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "OpenSSH Native Format",
      "variable": "pemHeader",
      "description": "OpenSSH native binary (inside base64): magic='openssh-key-v1'+(null) + cipher(string) + kdf(string) + kdf_options(string) + n_keys(uint32) + public_keys[n_keys] + encrypted_block { checkint(uint32,repeated) + private_keys[] + padding }. KDF 'bcrypt' uses bcrypt_pbkdf for key derivation."
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "Passphrase Protection",
      "variable": "firstByte",
      "description": "Unprotected keys: cipher='none', kdf='none'. Protected (modern): cipher='aes256-ctr', kdf='bcrypt'. Protected (legacy PEM): Proc-Type: 4,ENCRYPTED + DEK-Info: AES-128-CBC,<IV> headers before base64. No passphrase = immediate key extraction without any cracking."
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "Starts with PEM hyphen",
      "expression": "firstByte == 45",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "SSH private key file must start with '-' (0x2D) for PEM armor header. Non-PEM formats are not detected here."
    },
    {
      "name": "Header contains PRIVATE",
      "expression": "pemHeader != ''",
      "severity": "warning",
      "message": "Could not determine SSH private key format from header."
    }
  ],
  "navigation": {
    "bookmarks": [
      { "name": "PEM Header", "offset": 0, "color": "#FF4444" }
    ]
  },
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "SSH-KEY",
    "primaryField": "pemHeader",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "title": "Key Header",
        "icon": "",
        "fields": [ "firstByte", "pemHeader" ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "SSH Key Summary (Text)",
      "format": "text",
      "fields": [ "pemHeader" ]
    },
    {
      "name": "SSH Key Metadata (JSON)",
      "format": "json",
      "fields": [ "firstByte", "pemHeader" ]
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "category": "certificate",
    "riskLevel": "high",
    "notes": "SSH private key files are the most sensitive credential type on Unix/Linux systems. Unprotected keys (no passphrase) allow immediate authentication to any server that trusts the corresponding public key. Legacy PEM keys with Proc-Type/DEK-Info may use weak MD5-based key derivation. OpenSSH native format with bcrypt KDF is significantly more resistant to brute-force attacks. Never store private keys in version control, container images, or shared storage.",
    "suspiciousPatterns": [
      "Absence of 'Proc-Type: 4,ENCRYPTED' in legacy PEM = unencrypted private key — immediate compromise risk",
      "OpenSSH format with cipher=none in base64 content = unencrypted key despite modern format",
      "Private key files with world-readable permissions (chmod 644) are a critical security misconfiguration",
      "id_rsa files with very small file sizes may indicate 512 or 1024-bit RSA — cryptographically weak"
    ]
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "OpenSSH native (-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----): base64 decodes to: magic(15B 'openssh-key-v1')+00 + ciphername(string: 4B len + data) + kdfname(string) + kdfoptions(string) + n_keys(4B) + pubkey(string) + privkey_blob(string). Legacy PKCS#1 RSA PEM: base64 decodes to DER SEQUENCE { version INTEGER(0) + n,e,d,p,q,dp,dq,qi INTEGER (RSA private key components) }. Passphrase-protected legacy: PEM headers Proc-Type: 4,ENCRYPTED + DEK-Info: cipher,IV before base64.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Identify key format from PEM header: OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY (modern) vs RSA/EC/PRIVATE KEY (legacy)",
      "For legacy PEM keys: check for Proc-Type and DEK-Info headers indicating passphrase protection",
      "For OpenSSH native: decode base64, verify magic 'openssh-key-v1', read cipher and kdf fields",
      "Absence of passphrase protection (cipher=none or no Proc-Type) is a critical security finding",
      "Check file permissions if accessible — private keys should be chmod 600 (owner read-only)",
      "For RSA keys: assess key size by measuring the modulus integer length (2048 bits minimum, 4096 preferred)"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "OpenSSH — ssh-keygen, ssh-add for key management",
    "PuTTYgen — converts between OpenSSH and PuTTY PPK format",
    "openssl — openssl rsa -in key.pem -text -noout for RSA key inspection",
    "ssh-keygen -y — extracts public key from private key file",
    "ssh-audit — audits SSH key and server configuration"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Certificates",
    "extensions": [ ".pem", ".key", ".id_rsa", ".id_ed25519" ],
    "relatedFormats": [ "PEM", "PKCS12", "PGP_BINARY", "SSH_KNOWN_HOSTS" ],
    "note": "SSH private keys are used for authentication. The corresponding public key is appended to ~/.ssh/authorized_keys on target servers. Host private keys are stored in /etc/ssh/ (ssh_host_rsa_key, etc.). PuTTY uses a different .ppk format."
  },
  "MimeTypes": [
    "application/x-pem-file",
    "text/plain",
    "application/octet-stream"
  ],
  "UseCases": [
    "SSH authentication to remote servers without passwords",
    "Git operations with SSH authentication (GitHub, GitLab)",
    "Ansible and automation framework remote access",
    "SFTP file transfer authentication",
    "Signed git commits and tags via SSH signing (OpenSSH 8.0+)"
  ],
  "QualityMetrics": {
    "CompletenessScore": 88,
    "DocumentationLevel": "detailed",
    "BlocksDefined": 4,
    "ValidationRules": 2,
    "LastUpdated": "2026-04-15",
    "PriorityFormat": false,
    "AutoRefined": false
  },
  "TechnicalDetails": {
    "Format": "PEM-encoded (base64 + armor headers), text file",
    "ModernHeader": "-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----",
    "LegacyHeaders": "RSA PRIVATE KEY (PKCS#1), EC PRIVATE KEY (SEC1), PRIVATE KEY (PKCS#8)",
    "OpenSSHMagic": "6F70656E7373682D6B65792D76310A (openssh-key-v1 + LF)",
    "KeyTypes": "RSA, ECDSA (P-256/384/521), Ed25519, FIDO sk-ssh-ed25519, sk-ecdsa",
    "PassphraseKDF": "bcrypt (modern, OpenSSH native), MD5 (legacy PEM DEK-Info)"
  }
}
